puzzle.description:
Given a tree and an integer. Find all the nodes that are equal to the integer and give the sum of their direct children. (Leaf count as 0).

f8 :: Tree Int -> Int -> Int
hints: It's similar to the task we solved: Create list of tuples (node, left child, right child) for odd numbers

testCases.input: print $ f8 (Node 3 (Node 1 Leaf Leaf) (Node 1 Leaf Leaf)) 3

puzzle.description:
Reverse a tree.
Write a function to create mirror image of a tree.

Example: See task 0 in HW.
hints: How can we construct a new tree using the idea of flipping all left and right subtrees?

testCases.input: reverseTree (Node 1 (Node 2  (Node 4 Leaf Leaf)   (Node 5 Leaf Leaf))  (Node 3 (Node 6 Leaf Leaf)  Leaf))
testCases.expectedOutput: Node 1 (Node 3 Leaf (Node 6 Leaf Leaf)) (Node 2 (Node 5 Leaf Leaf) (Node 4 Leaf Leaf))
